==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heptad
<hw>Hep"tad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>heptas</ets>
the number seven. Gr. <?/, <?/, fr. <grk>"epta`</grk> seven.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An atom which has a valence of seven, and which
can be theoretically combined with, substituted for, or replaced by,
<xex>seven</xex> monad atoms or radicals; <as>as, iodine is a
<ex>heptad</ex> in iodic acid</as>. Also used as an adjective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heptade</ent>⟦br⟧
